# cells_iching.def -- I Ching trigram logic (radix-8)
#
# The oldest binary system in human history.
#
# 3,000 years before Leibniz. 5,000 years before Shannon.
# The eight trigrams (八卦, bāguà) encode all combinations
# of three yin/yang lines. Leibniz saw them in 1703 and
# recognised binary arithmetic. He wrote to the Jesuit
# Joachim Bouvet: "this is the origin of my binary calculus."
#
# Shannon formalised binary logic in 1938.
# Takahe generalised beyond binary in 2026.
# This .def file closes the loop.
#
# The eight trigrams:
#   0 = ☷ KUN   (Earth)     000  receptive
#   1 = ☶ GEN   (Mountain)  001  keeping still
#   2 = ☵ KAN   (Water)     010  the abysmal
#   3 = ☴ XUN   (Wind)      011  the gentle
#   4 = ☳ ZHEN  (Thunder)   100  the arousing
#   5 = ☲ LI    (Fire)      101  the clinging
#   6 = ☱ DUI   (Lake)      110  the joyous
#   7 = ☰ QIAN  (Heaven)    111  the creative
#
# Two trigrams form a hexagram (卦, guà). There are 64
# hexagrams — the same as 6-bit binary, the same as the
# number of codons in DNA. The universe rhymes.
#
# A changing line transforms one trigram into another by
# flipping a single bit. This is a truth table operation.
# The Book of Changes is, and always has been, a lookup
# table with commentary.

# ---- I Ching NOT: complement (all lines change) ----
# ☷ Earth (000) ↔ ☰ Heaven (111)
# ☶ Mountain (001) ↔ ☱ Lake (110)
# ☵ Water (010) ↔ ☲ Fire (101)
# ☴ Wind (011) ↔ ☳ Thunder (100)
#
# Every yin becomes yang, every yang becomes yin.
# The fundamental duality. 陰陽.

cell NOT radix 8 inputs 1 outputs 1
  pin A in
  pin Y out complement(A)
  truth 0 -> 7
  truth 1 -> 6
  truth 2 -> 5
  truth 3 -> 4
  truth 4 -> 3
  truth 5 -> 2
  truth 6 -> 1
  truth 7 -> 0
end

# ---- I Ching HEXAGRAM: combine two trigrams ----
# Lower trigram + upper trigram → hexagram index (0-63)
# lower * 8 + upper
# King Wen's sequence would be a different mapping,
# but the binary encoding is what Leibniz recognised.

cell HEXAGRAM radix 8 inputs 2 outputs 1
  pin LOWER in
  pin UPPER in
  pin HEX out hex(LOWER,UPPER)
  truth 0 0 ->  0
  truth 0 1 ->  1
  truth 0 2 ->  2
  truth 0 3 ->  3
  truth 0 4 ->  4
  truth 0 5 ->  5
  truth 0 6 ->  6
  truth 0 7 ->  7
  truth 1 0 ->  8
  truth 1 1 ->  9
  truth 1 2 -> 10
  truth 1 3 -> 11
  truth 1 4 -> 12
  truth 1 5 -> 13
  truth 1 6 -> 14
  truth 1 7 -> 15
  truth 2 0 -> 16
  truth 2 1 -> 17
  truth 2 2 -> 18
  truth 2 3 -> 19
  truth 2 4 -> 20
  truth 2 5 -> 21
  truth 2 6 -> 22
  truth 2 7 -> 23
  truth 3 0 -> 24
  truth 3 1 -> 25
  truth 3 2 -> 26
  truth 3 3 -> 27
  truth 3 4 -> 28
  truth 3 5 -> 29
  truth 3 6 -> 30
  truth 3 7 -> 31
  truth 4 0 -> 32
  truth 4 1 -> 33
  truth 4 2 -> 34
  truth 4 3 -> 35
  truth 4 4 -> 36
  truth 4 5 -> 37
  truth 4 6 -> 38
  truth 4 7 -> 39
  truth 5 0 -> 40
  truth 5 1 -> 41
  truth 5 2 -> 42
  truth 5 3 -> 43
  truth 5 4 -> 44
  truth 5 5 -> 45
  truth 5 6 -> 46
  truth 5 7 -> 47
  truth 6 0 -> 48
  truth 6 1 -> 49
  truth 6 2 -> 50
  truth 6 3 -> 51
  truth 6 4 -> 52
  truth 6 5 -> 53
  truth 6 6 -> 54
  truth 6 7 -> 55
  truth 7 0 -> 56
  truth 7 1 -> 57
  truth 7 2 -> 58
  truth 7 3 -> 59
  truth 7 4 -> 60
  truth 7 5 -> 61
  truth 7 6 -> 62
  truth 7 7 -> 63
end

# ---- I Ching ELEMENT: trigram → element mapping ----
# 0=Earth, 1=Metal, 2=Water, 3=Wood, 4=Wood, 5=Fire, 6=Metal, 7=Heaven/Metal
# Simplified wuxing (五行) cycle.

cell ELEMENT radix 8 inputs 1 outputs 1
  pin TRIGRAM in
  pin WUXING out element(TRIGRAM)
  truth 0 -> 0
  truth 1 -> 1
  truth 2 -> 2
  truth 3 -> 3
  truth 4 -> 3
  truth 5 -> 4
  truth 6 -> 1
  truth 7 -> 1
end

# ---- I Ching DFF ----

cell DFF radix 8 inputs 1 outputs 1
  pin D in
  pin Q out D
  truth 0 -> 0
  truth 1 -> 1
  truth 2 -> 2
  truth 3 -> 3
  truth 4 -> 4
  truth 5 -> 5
  truth 6 -> 6
  truth 7 -> 7
end

# ---- I Ching CONST ----

cell CONST radix 8 inputs 0 outputs 1
  pin Y out
  truth -> 0
  truth -> 1
  truth -> 2
  truth -> 3
  truth -> 4
  truth -> 5
  truth -> 6
  truth -> 7
end

# Leibniz to Bouvet, 1703:
# "What I find most remarkable is that this arithmetic
# by 0 and 1 happens to contain the mystery of the lines
# of an ancient Chinese king and philosopher named Fuxi."
#
# He was right. The I Ching IS binary arithmetic.
# And binary arithmetic is just radix-2 truth tables.
# And truth tables are just .def files.
# And .def files are just text.
#
# 伏羲 drew lines in the dirt 5,000 years ago.
# We're still executing them.
